      • getUnboundVariables

        public Set<Variable> getUnboundVariables()
        Returns any unbound variables. A bound variable is a varible in the clause that appears at least once in a positive literal with a StandardPredicate.

        If all Variables are bound, then DatabaseQueries can identify all groundings of the clause with possibly non-zero truth values in a Database.

        Returns:
        an unmodifiable set containing any unbound variables, or an empty set.
